                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>will be the sooner <sic>discoverd</sic>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">We are getting along shortly<lb/> here, the people are lukewarm<lb/>\n                and pernicious, and a few have<lb/> to stand the lament of expense,<lb/> in our\n                congregation.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Things did look very squally<lb/> at the date of <persName>Mr.\n                    Touro's</persName> last<lb/> letter to you, but I am happy<lb/> to say that\n                things look a<lb/> good deal better now.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">As the <persName role=\"author\">revd. Nathan</persName> has just<lb/>\n                this moment come in my office<lb/> I shall make him fill the<lb/> rest of this\n                sheet</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am my dear friend</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">yours ever faithfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Gershom K</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"Note:\"> The following is a clipping from the <hi rend=\"underline\">Picayune</hi>\n                that is attached to page 2.</p>\n            <p>luc, <persName>Genibrel</persName>, <persName>Graat</persName> and\n                    <persName>Scott</persName> in the chief charac-<lb/> ters.</p>\n            <p>———</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">TOKEN OF RESPECT.—We see the Hebrew<lb/> congregation in\n                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> have presented the<lb/>\n                <persName>Rev. Isaac Leeser</persName>, who has been their pastor for<lb/>\n                twenty-one years, with an elegant service of plate,<lb/> consisting of a pair of\n                pitchers, a pair of salvers,<lb/> and half a dozen goblets, all of the most\n                splendid<lb/> workmanship. Suitable inscriptions express the<lb/> high appreciation\n                which the donors have of the<lb/> abilities and labors of their minister. The\n                    <persName>Rev.<lb/> Mr. Leeser</persName> is the editor of the “Occident,”\n                and<lb/> the important services which he has rendered to<lb/> his brethren in this\n                country are, we believe, uni-<lb/>versally admitted.</p>\n            <p>———</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">NEW MUSIC.—We have received the following<lb/> from <persName>Tyler\n                    &amp; Hewitt</persName>, <placeName>No. 39 Camp <sic>street</sic></placeName>:\n                Xaupi's</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v40kk4q/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
