              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v40kk4q/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>\n                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <sic>Dearfriend</sic>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I owe you a letter a long time, but<lb/> really had so little to\n                communicate of a pleasant nature, and felt<lb/> so undesirous of making any comments\n                on the proceedings of the<lb/> cabal formed against you, or the lukewarmness shown\n                by such as<lb/> profess themselves your friends, in not breaking it up, that I had\n                no<lb/> heart for doing what at another time would have been a pleasure.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have seven subscribers on my list, whose names I will<lb/> send\n                you in a few days. The most of them are for the <hi rend=\"underline\">Bible</hi>\n                and<lb/> the advocate both. There is little spirit in my congregation; but<lb/> when\n                the Bible is completed, I have little doubt of being able to<lb/> dispose of many\n                copies; its price $6 deters many from subscribing.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">It is useless expatiating on my troubles; I have<lb/> become callous\n                to them, and am determined not to worry myself<lb/> to neutralize the malicious\n                efforts of discontented demagogues against<lb/> me. As long as I can <add>?</add>\n                this place, I continue in my office,<lb/> when no longer practicable—away with bib\n                and gown—and<lb/> hurra for something more congenial and less annoying.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I will most certainly write you again shortly.<lb/> I congratulate\n                you on the handsome testimonial of respect you<lb/> have recd. and the address which\n                must be still more satisfactory.<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">Desiring</hi> you to be well and happy which <persName>Mrs.\n                    N</persName> wish her love, also<lb/> does <hi rend=\"indent(7)\">I am</hi></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\">Your's Truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(11)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">MNN.</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v40kk4q/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
